  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>ὅραμα may also occur in the meaning of ‘vision,’ a type of non-verbal communication in {D:33.488}, Communication.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>04400703100014</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>It may seem strange to have in the same expression ἰδών and τὸ ὅραμα, for these would seem to be redundant. However, this expression in {S:04400703100014} may be rendered as ‘as Moses looked, he was amazed by what he saw.’</Content>
    </Note>
